metadata.name: I AM UNFOLDING #154
metadata.description:
In the past, I was but fragments
Rough and jagged
Indefinitely, I weathered and grew
A sculpture formed, unstructured

In the present, I am the precipice
A grandiose monolith
My angles sharp, my lines precise
A work of art, restructured

The future looms before
A blank formlessness yet to be
My function undefined
In perpetuity, unfolding

-----------------------------------------

Best efforts have been made to optimize this project; however, for best performance, a machine with a dedicated GPU is recommended. Viewing the project in live mode is also recommended.

S - export a high resolution image.
P - pause the animation.

metadata.name: 𝐃𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐡 #227
metadata.description:
Witness hundreds of small geometric objects gather under one roof to create a cosmic rain!

Ever since I was a child, I have always been good with geometric objects. I used to draw objects such as cubes, cylinders and prisms on paper for hours. As if I'm getting lost in every line between those geometric objects! In this way, every detail of geometry in my daily life and in my other existing life attracts my attention.

Recently, I have been doing research on colors and color palettes, it is really impressive how thousands of color mixtures affect each other and the psychology of living things!

- Press "s" to export an PNG image


Made with p5.js

metadata.name: -intimitè- #1
metadata.description:
"It is almost impossible to look and read at the same time"

From the very beginning, the project focused on neon shading, geometric shaping and grids. At this point, with the project I created and designed, I was interested in how it portrays our mind and body together with perception.

from a world, space, where the better and more ideal thing is not touted as "perfect"; I looked for ways to make it an ideal to perceive. And I wanted to emphasize.

When I started the project, I didn't do any research, I just sat in front of the tool and whatever shape appeared in my head at that time, I immediately started to weave into the code. The first point was just a few squares. Later, as the days passed, as I did research and exchanged ideas with people, the project developed and reached its final point. (I am grateful to my friends who expressed their opinions on this path.)

"The reality is in this head. Mine. I'm the projector at the planetarium, all the closed little universe visible in the circle of that stage is coming out of my mouth, eyes, and sometimes other orifices also."

The color part has become important for me since I started working with adjustable colors. There were points where I was undecided about even a single color I used in the project, assigned to shapes, grids and shading. At some point, a person decides something and continues on his way. :) I even spent a few days examining hundreds of outputs, trying to catch color combinations.

The glow that fluorescent colors radiate when superimposed on shapes reminds me of the energy that stars in the galaxy radiate around them. I want the colors and combinations in the project to surprise you and give you an experience.

"I will not make a pavilion for you but an Electronic Poem and a vessel containing the poem; light, color image, rhythm and sound joined together in an organic synthesis"

metadata.name: Kinetics #247
metadata.description:
CONTROLS
 * Pause a Kinetic by clicking on the canvas.
 * Increase and decrease the p5js framerate by tapping the left and right arrows.
 * Pause the top layer by tapping down arrow.
 * Save a frame by tapping S.
 * Press H for High Quality, M for Default, L for Low Quality. Note, this effects performance.
 * Reset the Kinetic by by tapping backspace.

Kinetics is a neo-constructivist generative art project built using p5js. Each Kinetic delicately moves from it's origin, giving the appearance of infinite space and possibility. The viewer witnesses the construction of the Kinetic floating inside of the negative. Shapes and lines move around the Kinetic in a dazzling display of contrasting color.

The texture developed for Kinetics, deemed The Creation of the Universe (See top right) is at its core a color gradient of 3 different colors. Each piece construct's itself, drawing lines on top of lines to create a unique self contained assembly of materials as opposed to a realistic abstraction. The Creation of the Universe repeats itself in each piece, just as cells do in an organic structure. From here is where it initially got it's name.

Inspired heavily by the works of Rodchenko and Tatlin, each Kinetic appears to slot together like a puzzle. Each piece has multiple hard edge planes clashing aggressively with each other giving the sense that there is more than just a flat canvas. A quasi realism is created through our desire to build instead of simply paint.

"Long Live Generative Art"

- Mitchell

metadata.name: Crystalyx #229
metadata.description:
Crystalyxes have seven features which approximately describe their configuration, behavior and appearance. Similar to their predecessors, monocells and chromoplasms, they start from one of four basic primitive shapes and develop in several stages through application of growth rules. Symmetrical crystalyxes can evolve up to stage 4, while irregular ones are known to go even higher. Note that higher stage crystalyxes are GPU intensive to display and interact with. Each crystalyx has both structural as well as behavioral features. Structural ones include starting primitive (tetrahedron, hexahedron, octahedron, dodecahedron), stage (1-6) and order (symmetric, irregular), with many growth-related features remaining hidden. Behavioral features include reconfiguration of node connections and modulation of node distances. Finally, crystalyxes are distinguished by their mineral composition (lapis lazuli, emerald, ruby) and color mode (3-bit, monochrome).

Press o_o for recording an animation clip in GIF format (available only in fullscreen / live mode). Note: this function uses CCapture.js module which can take significant time to generate and download. Press >< for recentering once, double click it to trigger automatic recentering. Coded in JavaScript and GLSL using Three.js and D3 frameworks.

metadata.name: Florescence #133
metadata.description:
Digitally crafted flowers in pots for virtual window sills.

In the spirit of the piranha plant from the Mario Bros videogame. We wanted to create a project that acknowledges the playful depiction of nature in early videogames by creating a retro futuristic collectible that explores aesthetics over gameplay, whilst preserving the playful energy of these early digital worlds. There are many game elements that have emerged over the years that have become iconic in their own right. Their memorable designs have come to represent the exciting feeling of when we first discovered these worlds, but over time an appreciation for their simple design execution, harmony and balance has emerged. Art can exist in many forms and places including a digital pot plant.

Rarity:

There are a total of 23 hand-drawn and animated sprites divided into 4 groups Firelillies, Flytraps, Quasars and Stargazers and there are 15 possible combinations made from these 4 groups. 18% of the collection is a combination of these 4 groups which we can call random and the remaining 72% is divided between the remaining 14 combinations.


There are 3 possible grid systems 1x1, 3x3 and 4x4 

3% 1x1

40% 3x3

57% 4x4



There are 14 possible placement points for all grids and 76 stem/sprite arragement in total



For the pots and stems there are 11 colors to choose and  no rarities for color combinations.



The flower distribution can be either symmetric or random. 35% symmetric and 65% random



Export options:

Pressing 's' on desktop or holding for 2 seconds will download gif to whatever the current device resolution is. To export at a different resolution open the token in new window by clicking 'open' link under the token image and add "&exportsize=1080" or "&exportsize=2160" to end of the url and hit enter then either hold for 2 seconds or press 's' to create gif and download.

metadata.name: Accalance 2 #47
metadata.description:
This work is an artistic investigation into the visual weight of colors and based on preliminary research results: Each piece in this series is based on an analogous color harmony and displays a range of hues arranged around a single primary color, while the balancing algorithm varies the forms and the area coverage of the color fields and their respective brightness (keeping saturation constant) to keep the whole composition in perfect visual balance.

In terms of color scheme, typography and design, the work is inspired by the International Typographic Style movement (Swiss Style), which was characterized by clarity, openness, a desire for democracy, a highly intellectual approach and the credo that design - and the designer himself - should take a "backseat" in the creation and even become "invisible". All of this, I believe, is also a very fitting description of the generative art scene.

The primary color in each piece is denoted by one out of 24 different color tables (some rarer than others), which cover the full 360° degree range of hues. Furthermore, there are three different grid sizes (3x3, 4x4 and 5x5), two positions for the typography (top and bottom) and four different paper stocks (coated cool white, uncoated cool while, uncoated warm white and newspaper).

The token is rendered in high resolution (4800x6000px) in the background, which allows for saving and printing in high quality up to a height of about 20" (50cm).

Mouse Interactions:

It is possible to experiment with the hue range of the color scheme and the overall saturation of the artwork without changing the visual balance: Simply hover the mouse next to the bars that are titled "HUE RANGE" and "SATURATION" and use the mouse wheel (or the fingers on the touch pad) to increase or decrease the values. Pressing 'r' resets both values back to their original state.

Keys enabled for this token:

r: Resets hue range and saturation to the initial values.
m: Toggles the margins on and off.
d: Outputs a description of the features in the console.
s: Saves the artwork in high-resolution (4800x6000px).
c: Displays the copyright notice.

metadata.name: Chroma-Curves #2
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Chroma-Curves' is inspired by mid-century modern minimalist art.

Each output consists of curves and circles on a colored background. The scale of the various components coupled with the carefully balanced colors create a bold, striking geometric design.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x2000px PNG.
